What’s Next with Aki Anastasiou is South Africa’s most popular technology talk show, and the ideal platform to position your business as a leader in the ICT market. As part of the MyBroadband group, we make it easy for companies and their executives to get featured on the show. This is possible through: All What’s Next interviews are published to the What’s Next website, MyBroadband, YouTube, Facebook, and Spotify – reaching an engaged audience. A season sponsorship then provides the participating company with exclusive brand exposure across both the What’s Next and MyBroadband platforms. What’s Next with Aki Anastasiou has hosted the biggest names in technology, including Vodacom CEO Shameel Joosub, former MTN SA CEO Godfrey Motsa, Dimension Data founder Jeremy Ord, Microsoft SA CEO Lillian Barnard, Sygnia CEO Magda Wierzycka, Discovery CEO Adrian Gore, FNB CEO Jacques Celliers, Capitec Bank CEO Gerrie Fourie, Afrihost CEO Gian Visser, and Dell SA MD Doug Woolley. Season sponsors have included Discovery Bank, Infobip, Sage, Microsoft, Syspro, and Accenture. For more information about the show and how to take part, contact MyBroadband Sales Director Cara Muller on cara@mybroadband.co.za